children.text: The data cables are crossing, or in direct contact with the electrical wiring.
The relevant Australian Standard AS/NZS 3000 Wiring Rules, clause 3.9.8.4 Proximity to Non-Electrical Services states that
‘Wiring systems shall maintain a separation of not less than 50mm from any above ground telecommunications cabling’
These telecommunication (data) cables and the electrical wiring need to be separated from each other at all locations using either a barrier/conduit, or by providing a minimum of 50mm separation.
